Movie Men records movies we watch.

Docker setup includes:
- `nginx` (port `8080`)
- `php-fpm` (runs the PHP app)
- `mariadb` (database)
- webroot at `public/`

## Run with Docker

1. Copy env file:
   `cp .env.example .env`
2. Start containers:
   `docker compose up --build -d`
3. Open:
   `http://localhost:8080`

## Database initialization

If you have schema/data SQL, put it in:
`docker/mariadb/init/`

MariaDB will execute any `*.sql` file in that folder when the DB volume is first created.

If you need to re-run init scripts from scratch:
`docker compose down -v && docker compose up --build -d`

## App DB config

In Docker, the app reads:
- `DB_HOST`
- `DB_USER`
- `DB_PASSWORD`
- `DB_NAME`

## Poster files from old server

Copy your old poster image files into:
`storage/posters/`

Expected naming pattern is:
- `orig_<movie_id>.jpg`
- `disp_<movie_id>.jpg`
- `thum_<movie_id>.jpg`

(`.jpg` can be changed with `POSTERS_IMAGE_FORMAT` in `.env`.)

Temporary download files are written to:
`storage/tmp/`

## Read-only mode

`READ_ONLY_MODE=1` (default) disables login.
Set `READ_ONLY_MODE=0` to enable login.
